cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper deals with using deep learning methods to analyze video data and extract valuable information by classifying image frames and detecting objects. Specifically, it focuses on using Siamese Networks to monitor railway tracks and detect significant assets like switches on the track. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to detect abnormalities on the railway track and robotics (cs.RO) to monitor the track using video feed from a moving locomotive. Finally, the paper also involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) to learn the similarity between images and detect differences between them.
